<xref href="https://mediaguide.cpp.canon/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/</xref>. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">Line or text sharpness can be influenced by spreading of ink on the media and/or the distance of the media relative to the printheads. In case of spreading the ink droplets are positioned well, but the ink spreads too much before it is cured by the UV-lamps (see close up A (left)). This can be caused by the media surface itself or the time between positioning and curing. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the printhead height relative to the media is incorrect the ink droplets are not positioned well and will create a “ghost”-like image (see close up B (right)). 
</p><fig id="GUID-DF5C70F0-F1E8-4F34-BA0D-441BADF7FD4D" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Close-up (A - left, B - Right)</title><image href="GUID-0F0F5D75-BDC9-4CBE-A8D0-F64A3E49F1A3-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0F0F5D75-BDC9-4CBE-A8D0-F64A3E49F1A3-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Figure 1:A) Close up of ink spreading , B) Droplet position
